        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3"><summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors"><h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Can I finance a private sale used car?</h3><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg></summary><div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100"><p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Yes. Most lenders finance private sale purchases. You will need a PPSR check, current market valuation, and vehicle details. Pre-approval lets you act quickly and negotiate from strength.</p></div></details>
        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3"><summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors"><h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Is there a maximum vehicle age for finance?</h3><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg></summary><div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100"><p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">It varies by lender. Some cap at 7 years old at end of loan term, others at 10-12 years, and some have no maximum age. Nik Finance matches your vehicle to lenders who will finance it.</p></div></details>
        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3"><summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors"><h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Should I get a used car inspected before buying?</h3><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg></summary><div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100"><p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Always. A pre-purchase inspection costs $150-300 and can reveal hidden mechanical issues, accident damage, or safety concerns that could cost thousands to fix. Most lenders also require the vehicle to be roadworthy.</p></div></details>
        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3"><summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors"><h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">Do I need a deposit for a used car loan?</h3><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg></summary><div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100"><p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">No deposit is required with many lenders for borrowers with good credit. A deposit can help with older vehicles or less-than-perfect credit by reducing lender risk and potentially securing a better rate.</p></div></details>
